115.4	Stoicism	Stoicism	Stoicism (Greek Στωικισμός) is a school of Hellenistic philosophy founded in Athens by Zeno of Citium in the early . The Stoics taught that destructive emotions resulted from errors in judgement, and that a sage, or person of "moral and intellectual perfection," would not suffer such emotions.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/41/Zeno_of_Citium_pushkin.jpg/220px-Zeno_of_Citium_pushkin.jpg
